item.description:
Note: Starting in Go 1.17, installing executables with go get is deprecated. go install may be used instead. In Go 1.18, go get will no longer build packages&hellip;
In other words, go get in 1.18 and beyond will no longer install executables. Use go install
 Go has an impressive number of command line tools integreated into go &lt;tool_name&gt; that us developers use daily. You can get a list of them by

to launch evans on localhost and port 8080: evans --host localhost --port 8080 -r repl
to list all rpc services: show service Note: if in above step, you see nothing, probably you are in the wrong package. Services belong to a package. Switch to the right package by show package and then choose the package by package &lt;package_name&gt;
call an rpc named: Login call Login (you will be prompted to fill out the request object params)
